    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-05-01T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-05-01T09:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/5–150: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">All Diplomatic Missions and Certain Consular Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d5fn1">Transmitted to all Embassies and Legations; to the
                        High Commissioner, Germany; to the United States Political Adviser, Tokyo;
                        and to consular officers at Algiers, Dakar, Hong Kong, Singapore, Taipei,
                        Tripoli, and Rabat.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-05-01T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 1, 1950—10 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dept interested receiving regular reports on press and other public reaction
                    abroad to Hoover<note n="2" xml:id="d5fn2">Ex-President Herbert Hoover.</note>
                    proposal for org of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> without the participation
                    of Commie countries.</p>
                <p>Dept desires initial report soonest.<note n="3" xml:id="d5fn3">Relevant
                        documentation is located in the 310.2 file.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Transmitted for info only to <gloss target="#t_AmEmb1">AmEmb</gloss> Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
